      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PARTY CENTRAL NZ (8) resumes following a spell of ten months and has joined the powerhouse Jason Grimson yard since last seen. Has a great fresh record with four wins and a placing from five first-up appearances. Must overcome a wide draw but should be ready to go off a nice trial. BETTORLIGHTEM UP (6) progressed of a resuming fourth to come from this barrier and finish third last week at this circuit and distance. Has won third-up before so should be close to peak fitness. VINKE B NZ (10) draws wide but has placed in two of his last four starts in stronger company so is better placed. TOORAM CEE CEE (2) showed pleasing improvement last time out when third from this barrier at Newcastle. Go well.",
